<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880115-0023 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Convergent Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CVGT </CO><TEXT>   Convergent Inc. said it expects to report a loss for the 1987 fourth quarter. A spokesman for the San Jose, Calif., business automation company refused to say why the company expects to report a loss, or to comment on expected revenue.    For the first nine months, Convergent had a loss of $8.7 million on revenue of $308.4 million.    In the year-earlier fourth quarter, Convergent had a loss of $4.5 million on revenue of $77.4 million. For 1986, the company had a loss of $32.8 million on revenue of $305.8 million.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Convergent closed at $3.8125 a share, down 6.25 cents.    Some analysts had expected that Convergent, which had a profit in the third quarter, would post a profit for the fourth quarter. </TEXT></DOC>